1
00:01:34,538 --> 00:01:37,537
[NARRATOR]
<i>Backed up by the newly restored</i>
<i>and automail equipped Lan Fan,</i>

2
00:01:37,537 --> 00:01:40,770
<i>Ed battles the Homunculus</i>
<i>known as Pride.</i>

3
00:01:40,804 --> 00:01:43,470
<i>As the fierce battle rages</i>
<i>towards the Promised Day,</i>

4
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:48,270
<i>Ed manages to safely retrieve</i>
<i>Al from Pride's clutches.</i>

5
00:01:48,304 --> 00:01:50,704
<i>Faced with the possibility</i>
<i>of losing the fight,</i>

6
00:01:50,737 --> 00:01:55,037
<i>Pride devours Gluttony in order</i>
<i>to obtain his abilities.</i>

7
00:01:56,804 --> 00:01:59,137
<i>Elsewhere, Colonel</i>
<i>Mustang joins up with</i>

8
00:01:59,170 --> 00:02:02,104
<i>Lieutenant Hawkeye to lead his</i>
<i>subordinates on a mission</i>

9
00:02:02,137 --> 00:02:06,337
<i>to kidnap the Fuhrer's wife</i>
<i>and take her as their hostage.</i>

10
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,051
[HOHENHEIM]
Al... Can you
hear me?

11
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:16,484
Come on...
Wake up!

12
00:02:16,518 --> 00:02:17,984
Alphonse!

13
00:02:18,484 --> 00:02:19,651
[PRIDE SNIFFS]

14
00:02:19,684 --> 00:02:21,684
I know that smell.

15
00:02:22,618 --> 00:02:25,451
[PRIDE]
Tell me something, Edward.

16
00:02:25,484 --> 00:02:27,518
Do you think your
father would step forward

17
00:02:27,551 --> 00:02:31,118
to save you if I chopped
off one of your limbs?

18
00:02:32,184 --> 00:02:34,151
[ED GRUNTING]

19
00:02:34,184 --> 00:02:35,384
[ED SCREAMING]

20
00:02:37,684 --> 00:02:39,284
[ED YELLS]

21
00:02:46,051 --> 00:02:47,451
[ED GROWLS]

22
00:02:48,618 --> 00:02:49,684
[PRIDE LAUGHS]

23
00:02:51,351 --> 00:02:52,618
Look out!

24
00:02:57,084 --> 00:02:58,084
[ED YELLS]

25
00:03:02,084 --> 00:03:05,484
[GREED GRUNTING]

26
00:03:06,751 --> 00:03:07,584
[LAN FAN]
Young Lord!

27
00:03:07,618 --> 00:03:09,184
Not quite.

28
00:03:09,218 --> 00:03:10,584
The name's Greed.

29
00:03:10,618 --> 00:03:11,451
[LAN FAN GASPS]

30
00:03:11,484 --> 00:03:12,151
It's you.

31
00:03:12,184 --> 00:03:14,118
Give the Prince
his body back!

32
00:03:14,151 --> 00:03:16,651
Now why would I wanna do
something like that...?

33
00:03:16,684 --> 00:03:17,351
Oh, boy.

34
00:03:17,384 --> 00:03:19,118
Heads up!

35
00:03:22,751 --> 00:03:24,351
[LAN FAN GROANS IN PAIN]

36
00:03:26,551 --> 00:03:28,084
[ED]
You alright?!

37
00:03:29,718 --> 00:03:31,051
[LAN FAN GASPS]

38
00:03:31,084 --> 00:03:32,151
[LAN FAN YELLS]

39
00:03:33,351 --> 00:03:34,484
[ED GRUNTS]

40
00:03:36,018 --> 00:03:37,251
I didn't ask
for your help.

41
00:03:37,284 --> 00:03:38,118
Oh, shut up...

42
00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:40,584
Your arm obviously
hasn't healed yet.

43
00:03:40,618 --> 00:03:41,618
[LAN FAN GASPS]

44
00:03:41,651 --> 00:03:43,484
I can take care of myself.

45
00:03:43,518 --> 00:03:46,618
Then prove it to me and
start acting like you can.

46
00:03:46,651 --> 00:03:48,451
We're gonna need
your help tomorrow.

47
00:03:48,484 --> 00:03:50,051
[LAN FAN GASPS]

48
00:03:50,084 --> 00:03:52,351
[HEINKEL GRUNTING]

49
00:03:52,384 --> 00:03:53,584
[GREED YELLS]

50
00:03:53,618 --> 00:03:55,084
Get him
out of here!

51
00:03:55,118 --> 00:03:57,518
Sorry I couldn't kill
the little bastard.

52
00:03:57,551 --> 00:03:58,218
[GREED LAUGHS]

53
00:03:58,251 --> 00:03:59,684
Don't sweat it.

54
00:03:59,718 --> 00:04:02,518
I can't exactly
fault you for that one.

55
00:04:02,551 --> 00:04:05,551
Even I consider
him to be a monster.

56
00:04:12,684 --> 00:04:16,051
[HOHENHEIM]
Wake up... Alphonse!

57
00:04:19,618 --> 00:04:22,384
[AL]
What...? Dad?

58
00:04:22,418 --> 00:04:23,651
Hey.

59
00:04:24,351 --> 00:04:27,184
[METAL CLANKS]

60
00:04:27,218 --> 00:04:31,218
So uh... Wait, I thought
you were in... Is this Kanama?

61
00:04:31,251 --> 00:04:33,084
That it is.

62
00:04:33,118 --> 00:04:36,151
But I was in the east...
So how did I...

63
00:04:36,184 --> 00:04:37,051
[AL GASPS]

64
00:04:37,084 --> 00:04:38,618
That's right...! Pride!

65
00:04:38,651 --> 00:04:43,051
Dad... The Homunculus Pride...
He took control of my body!

66
00:04:43,084 --> 00:04:46,151
I know... Mr. Gorius
told me all about it.

67
00:04:46,184 --> 00:04:47,484
[DARIUS]
It's Darius.

68
00:04:47,518 --> 00:04:51,484
It was... it was like he
was manipulating my soul...

69
00:04:51,518 --> 00:04:53,484
I feel violated.

70
00:04:53,518 --> 00:04:55,984
The Homunculi are
basically your relatives.

71
00:04:56,018 --> 00:04:59,284
They're like second
generation clones of me....

72
00:04:59,318 --> 00:05:01,718
So they might be able to
interfere with your seal

73
00:05:01,751 --> 00:05:03,384
since we share the same blood.

74
00:05:03,418 --> 00:05:05,184
[BUSHES RUSTLING]

75
00:05:06,984 --> 00:05:08,384
[AL]
Old man Fu?

76
00:05:08,418 --> 00:05:12,218
[FU BREATHING HEAVILY]

77
00:05:12,251 --> 00:05:15,184
Can you clean and
dress this man's wounds?

78
00:05:15,218 --> 00:05:17,518
How's everything
going over there?

79
00:05:17,551 --> 00:05:20,051
[FU]
I'm guessing you
must be Edward's father?

80
00:05:20,084 --> 00:05:21,284
That's correct.

81
00:05:21,318 --> 00:05:23,584
[FU GRUNTS]

82
00:05:23,618 --> 00:05:27,118
That shadow monster devoured
the fat Homunculus whole...

83
00:05:27,151 --> 00:05:29,118
and he's overpowering us.

84
00:05:29,151 --> 00:05:31,584
Greed and Edward are doing
everything they can...

85
00:05:31,618 --> 00:05:34,584
but I don't know how
long they can last.

86
00:05:35,618 --> 00:05:37,451
[AL THINKING]
<i>This is all my fault...</i>

87
00:05:37,484 --> 00:05:41,318
<i>None of this would've happened</i>
<i>if I hadn't let Pride catch me.</i>

88
00:05:43,018 --> 00:05:45,518
[FU]
The fires have given him all
the light he could wish for

89
00:05:45,551 --> 00:05:47,251
and I'm out
of flash bombs...

90
00:05:47,284 --> 00:05:50,251
We need a new
plan and fast.

91
00:05:50,284 --> 00:05:52,284
And not
just for us.

92
00:05:53,151 --> 00:05:54,318
[DARIUS]
The slum dwellers
are gonna be

93
00:05:54,351 --> 00:05:57,084
headed straight for
Pride any minute now.

94
00:05:58,451 --> 00:05:59,951
[AL]
Hey, Dad?

95
00:06:00,684 --> 00:06:03,418
You're a pretty
brilliant alchemist, right?

96
00:06:04,651 --> 00:06:08,151
I guess...
I know a thing or two.

97
00:06:08,184 --> 00:06:09,384
I've got an idea,

98
00:06:09,418 --> 00:06:12,084
but I'm gonna need
your help to pull it off.

99
00:06:12,118 --> 00:06:15,084
[ED AND GREED YELL]

100
00:06:16,251 --> 00:06:18,084
Now then...

101
00:06:18,118 --> 00:06:22,184
I can see you more clearly
without those trees in the way.

102
00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:26,251
[LAN FAN GASPS]

103
00:06:27,384 --> 00:06:29,451
There's not much point in
trying to hide from me...

104
00:06:29,484 --> 00:06:31,451
I can smell
each move you make.

105
00:06:31,484 --> 00:06:32,584
[GREED GRUNTS]

106
00:06:32,618 --> 00:06:35,484
[GREED]
Dammit... You still
breathin' over there?

107
00:06:35,518 --> 00:06:37,451
Does wheezing count?

108
00:06:37,484 --> 00:06:39,718
This isn't really the time
to worry about others,

109
00:06:39,751 --> 00:06:40,718
is it, Greed...?

110
00:06:40,751 --> 00:06:42,184
As soft as
you've become...

111
00:06:42,218 --> 00:06:45,318
I wonder how much
longer you can survive?

112
00:06:45,351 --> 00:06:47,218
Shut up, you beast.

113
00:06:47,251 --> 00:06:50,484
What a horrific thing to say
to your own brother, Greed...

114
00:06:50,518 --> 00:06:52,284
Honestly...

115
00:06:52,318 --> 00:06:54,151
I might have to eat you.

116
00:06:54,184 --> 00:06:57,518
I promise that I won't
go down easy... Brother.

117
00:06:59,584 --> 00:07:00,984
[PRIDE SNIFFS]

118
00:07:03,018 --> 00:07:05,951
[PRIDE]
Oh... So you've chosen
to show yourself.

119
00:07:05,984 --> 00:07:07,984
Eh, Hohenheim?

120
00:07:08,018 --> 00:07:10,384
The hero always waits
until the last second

121
00:07:10,418 --> 00:07:12,184
to make his move.

122
00:07:12,218 --> 00:07:14,384
Hero...? Interesting...

123
00:07:14,418 --> 00:07:17,318
You must think
you can defeat me.

124
00:07:17,351 --> 00:07:19,684
[HOHENHEIM]
No, I'd never think that.

125
00:07:19,718 --> 00:07:22,584
I'm not dumb enough
to try and fight you.

126
00:07:30,751 --> 00:07:33,518
[PRIDE THINKING]
<i>What could he possibly</i>
<i>be thinking...?</i>

127
00:07:33,551 --> 00:07:36,018
<i>He must be</i>
<i>plotting something.</i>

128
00:07:51,751 --> 00:07:53,451
<i>Here he comes!</i>

129
00:07:53,484 --> 00:07:56,951
[AL YELLS]

130
00:07:57,351 --> 00:08:01,351
Are you joking...?
This was your pathetic plan?

131
00:08:03,118 --> 00:08:06,651
You should have run
when you had the chance.

132
00:08:06,684 --> 00:08:07,684
[LOUD THUD]

133
00:08:07,718 --> 00:08:10,584
[METAL CLANKS]

134
00:08:10,618 --> 00:08:12,351
Al, no!

135
00:08:16,984 --> 00:08:18,284
[PRIDE LAUGHS]

136
00:08:18,318 --> 00:08:21,718
[PRIDE]
It seems as though your son
enjoys being held hostage.

137
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:25,218
It's either that,
or he's supremely stupid.

138
00:08:27,484 --> 00:08:30,151
That's crossing a line, Pride.

139
00:08:30,184 --> 00:08:32,118
Don't ever mock my son.

140
00:08:32,151 --> 00:08:36,218
[LOUD ELECTRICAL SOUNDS]

141
00:08:41,584 --> 00:08:43,118
[ED GASPS]

142
00:08:45,984 --> 00:08:47,318
[PRIDE GASPS]

143
00:08:47,351 --> 00:08:48,484
[PRIDE GRUNTS ANGRILY]

144
00:08:51,484 --> 00:08:55,351
Hohenheim!

145
00:09:07,151 --> 00:09:08,518
[GREED]
That's amazing.

146
00:09:08,551 --> 00:09:12,318
He actually managed
to confine Pride.

147
00:09:12,351 --> 00:09:13,684
[GREED LAUGHS]

148
00:09:20,184 --> 00:09:21,484
What the hell are
you doing...?!

149
00:09:21,518 --> 00:09:23,651
Al's trapped in there
with that monster...!

150
00:09:23,684 --> 00:09:26,184
How could you do
something like that?!

151
00:09:26,218 --> 00:09:28,318
It wasn't my idea.

152
00:09:28,351 --> 00:09:30,651
Al was the one
who suggested this.

153
00:09:30,684 --> 00:09:32,118
[ED GASPS]

154
00:09:33,451 --> 00:09:34,384
[AL LAUGHS]

155
00:09:34,418 --> 00:09:35,584
[AL]
You fell for it...!

156
00:09:35,618 --> 00:09:38,518
You can't use your
powers in this darkness.

157
00:09:38,551 --> 00:09:40,418
I don't see why
you're laughing...

158
00:09:40,451 --> 00:09:43,084
You're trapped inside
this thing too...

159
00:09:43,118 --> 00:09:45,251
As soon as you try to
make an opening to leave,

160
00:09:45,284 --> 00:09:47,518
I'll slice you into
little pieces...

161
00:09:47,551 --> 00:09:51,318
[AL]
I don't remember saying
anything about leaving.

162
00:09:51,351 --> 00:09:54,051
Let's have a little test
of endurance, Selim...

163
00:09:54,084 --> 00:09:57,318
Oh, sorry. Would you prefer
to be called Pride...?

164
00:09:57,351 --> 00:10:02,184
Ya'see, Pride, my body doesn't
need oxygen or light or food.

165
00:10:02,218 --> 00:10:04,318
I'm perfectly
comfortable right here

166
00:10:04,351 --> 00:10:06,184
until the Promised Day is over.

167
00:10:06,218 --> 00:10:09,984
And I'm gonna make sure that
you stay put no matter what.

168
00:10:11,151 --> 00:10:14,184
[HOHENHEIM]
It would've been nearly
impossible to defeat Pride...

169
00:10:14,218 --> 00:10:15,618
And it was only
a matter of time

170
00:10:15,651 --> 00:10:18,151
before the fight
spread to the slums...

171
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:20,318
Since we knew we
couldn't defeat him...

172
00:10:20,351 --> 00:10:23,684
I acted as a decoy
and we imprisoned him.

173
00:10:23,718 --> 00:10:25,351
We've bought
ourselves enough time

174
00:10:25,384 --> 00:10:27,251
to figure out how
to destroy him.

175
00:10:27,284 --> 00:10:29,151
[ED]
Well you could've at least
told me what you were--

176
00:10:29,184 --> 00:10:31,484
Your brother
told me not to...

177
00:10:31,518 --> 00:10:34,184
He said that you'd be
against it... Okay?

178
00:10:34,218 --> 00:10:35,451
[ED GASPS]

179
00:10:37,184 --> 00:10:39,984
Al came up with this plan
because it was the only way

180
00:10:40,018 --> 00:10:41,684
to make sure everyone
would survive...

181
00:10:41,718 --> 00:10:44,118
Try to understand.

182
00:10:45,984 --> 00:10:49,451
Now... Let's get to work
putting these fires out.

183
00:10:55,218 --> 00:10:56,184
[ED]
Al!

184
00:10:56,218 --> 00:10:57,118
[AL GASPS]

185
00:10:57,151 --> 00:10:58,351
[AL]
Brother!

186
00:11:00,684 --> 00:11:01,851
Hey, Al!

187
00:11:01,884 --> 00:11:05,918
[AL]
Sorry, Brother...
it's not much of reunion, huh?

188
00:11:07,484 --> 00:11:11,551
But... This is all my fault
so I had to do something.

189
00:11:11,584 --> 00:11:15,384
And besides... I only have to
stay in here for one day...

190
00:11:15,418 --> 00:11:18,018
I promise I'll be
okay, Brother.

191
00:11:23,251 --> 00:11:27,451
So Lust is dead...
Envy's gone... Gluttony's eaten.

192
00:11:27,484 --> 00:11:29,218
Wrath is at eastern command...

193
00:11:29,251 --> 00:11:31,651
and they've got
Pride under lockdown.

194
00:11:33,351 --> 00:11:34,551
[GREED GRUNTS]

195
00:11:35,218 --> 00:11:37,151
So that means
Sloth and Pops

196
00:11:37,184 --> 00:11:39,584
are the only ones
watching over Central.

197
00:11:39,618 --> 00:11:42,951
Hey, Greed...
What the hell are you planning?

198
00:11:42,984 --> 00:11:43,951
[GREED LAUGHS]

199
00:11:43,984 --> 00:11:45,418
[GREED]
I've told you.

200
00:11:45,451 --> 00:11:49,451
I'm planning on
ruling the entire world.

201
00:11:50,684 --> 00:11:52,684
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

202
00:11:57,222 --> 00:11:59,222
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

203
00:12:00,855 --> 00:12:03,188
[HOMELESS MAN 1]
Am I going crazy, or
have you guys noticed

204
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:05,388
all the Ishvalans
around lately?

205
00:12:05,422 --> 00:12:08,255
No, you're right. There's a
small army of them holed up

206
00:12:08,288 --> 00:12:10,655
in those buildings out
to the west of town.

207
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:12,688
And speakin' of Ishvalans,
ya have to wonder

208
00:12:12,722 --> 00:12:14,155
what ever happened
to that fellow

209
00:12:14,188 --> 00:12:17,655
with the x-shaped
scar across his face.

210
00:12:17,688 --> 00:12:18,822
[ALL THREE MEN GASP]

211
00:12:18,855 --> 00:12:21,422
[HOMELESS MAN 1]
Well, I guess you
can ask him yourself.

212
00:12:21,455 --> 00:12:24,222
[HOMELESS MAN 2]
Speak of the devil
and he shall appear.

213
00:12:24,255 --> 00:12:27,355
[SCAR]
Any of you know how to
get to the Kanama slums?

214
00:12:27,388 --> 00:12:30,588
[HOMELESS MAN 1]
Yeah, sure... Kanama is
just south of the city...

215
00:12:30,622 --> 00:12:32,788
right on the outskirts
of the forest.

216
00:12:32,822 --> 00:12:35,355
Is that so...
thank you.

217
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:39,222
[HOMELESS MAN 2]
Did that little girl ever
meet back up with you guys?

218
00:12:39,255 --> 00:12:40,622
You know,
the one that always

219
00:12:40,655 --> 00:12:42,522
carried that cat
around with her...

220
00:12:42,555 --> 00:12:45,222
She passed through here
again just a few weeks back.

221
00:12:45,255 --> 00:12:46,455
She did what?

222
00:12:46,488 --> 00:12:48,755
[GERSO]
It sounds like she didn't
go back to Xing after all.

223
00:12:48,788 --> 00:12:51,488
[ZAMPANO]
What the hell
is that girl doing?

224
00:12:51,522 --> 00:12:54,488
[HOMELESS MAN 4]
Well, well... You boys
out celebrating tonight?

225
00:12:54,522 --> 00:12:56,622
Why...? What's
to celebrate?

226
00:12:56,655 --> 00:12:59,522
You can drop the act...
I know you were behind

227
00:12:59,555 --> 00:13:01,455
blowing up the train
Bradley was on.

228
00:13:01,488 --> 00:13:02,488
What was that?

229
00:13:02,522 --> 00:13:04,922
So you...
You weren't behind it?

230
00:13:04,955 --> 00:13:06,255
[SCAR]
It's news to us.

231
00:13:06,288 --> 00:13:07,322
Well, huh...

232
00:13:07,355 --> 00:13:09,755
I just assumed you must've
led the other Ishvalans

233
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:12,188
to take your revenge
on King Bradley.

234
00:13:12,222 --> 00:13:14,255
All that stuff about
them bein' terrorists

235
00:13:14,288 --> 00:13:16,888
is nothin' but
paranoid nonsense.

236
00:13:16,922 --> 00:13:21,188
My brothers would never lower
themselves to such cowardice.

237
00:13:21,222 --> 00:13:22,455
They're your allies...

238
00:13:22,488 --> 00:13:26,588
And this country will soon see
them as heroes, not terrorists.

239
00:13:28,822 --> 00:13:33,822
[KIMBLEE HUMMING]

240
00:13:46,788 --> 00:13:48,655
[KIMBLEE]
I need to learn to
draw the line somewhere

241
00:13:48,688 --> 00:13:50,322
when it comes to my job.

242
00:13:50,355 --> 00:13:52,655
I spent a fortune having
this suit tailor-made

243
00:13:52,688 --> 00:13:54,488
and now it's filthy.

244
00:13:55,388 --> 00:13:59,388
And the fun isn't even scheduled
to start until the sun's up.

245
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:09,922
[AL]
That's pointless.

246
00:14:09,955 --> 00:14:12,222
I doubt my dad would've
made the walls thin enough

247
00:14:12,255 --> 00:14:14,622
for a child
to tunnel out.

248
00:14:19,922 --> 00:14:21,622
It's not that hard
to surprise you

249
00:14:21,655 --> 00:14:24,522
when you think so
little of us humans.

250
00:14:24,555 --> 00:14:26,622
You think you've got
us all figured out.

251
00:14:26,655 --> 00:14:28,355
But you don't know
a thing about us...

252
00:14:28,388 --> 00:14:32,788
You're too arrogant to see that
things might not go your way.

253
00:14:32,822 --> 00:14:35,155
Like your plan
to use us...

254
00:14:35,188 --> 00:14:37,755
It was too sloppy
to actually work.

255
00:14:37,788 --> 00:14:39,755
And how's that?

256
00:14:39,788 --> 00:14:42,555
Well... The plan
needed us, right...?

257
00:14:42,588 --> 00:14:44,455
As your
sacrifices...?

258
00:14:44,488 --> 00:14:47,588
The whole thing hinged on
us doing what you wanted...

259
00:14:47,622 --> 00:14:49,288
But what if we
had simply decided

260
00:14:49,322 --> 00:14:51,288
to run away to a
different country...?

261
00:14:51,322 --> 00:14:52,422
That's all it
would've taken,

262
00:14:52,455 --> 00:14:55,388
and your entire
plan falls apart.

263
00:14:56,922 --> 00:15:00,488
[PRIDE]
True... And there are some
humans selfish enough

264
00:15:00,522 --> 00:15:04,888
who would've done exactly
what you said... But then...

265
00:15:04,922 --> 00:15:09,388
Not all...
Just look at Wrath's wife.

266
00:15:09,422 --> 00:15:11,722
There was a time when we
took a trip to the city

267
00:15:11,755 --> 00:15:14,522
and I was almost run
over by a car...

268
00:15:14,555 --> 00:15:16,622
The car swerved of course...

269
00:15:16,655 --> 00:15:18,555
but not before
she risked her life

270
00:15:18,588 --> 00:15:21,488
trying to shield
me with her body.

271
00:15:21,522 --> 00:15:25,555
She had no idea that I could've
easily protected myself...

272
00:15:25,588 --> 00:15:27,222
but I was genuinely shocked

273
00:15:27,255 --> 00:15:30,388
by her selfless
concern for my safety.

274
00:15:32,455 --> 00:15:34,855
I've always known what
it was to have a father...

275
00:15:34,888 --> 00:15:37,788
but I have never had what
you would call a mother...

276
00:15:37,822 --> 00:15:41,722
I was quite intrigued by her
and how she cared for me...

277
00:15:41,755 --> 00:15:45,888
And I realized what it was
like to have a mother.

278
00:15:45,922 --> 00:15:50,355
When you say Wrath's wife...
You mean Mrs. Bradley, right?

279
00:15:50,388 --> 00:15:52,422
Yes, that is correct.

280
00:15:52,455 --> 00:15:53,588
[METAL CLANKS]

281
00:15:54,822 --> 00:15:57,355
How could you
deceive her all this time?

282
00:15:57,388 --> 00:16:00,888
I won't deny that I was
just playing house with her.

283
00:16:00,922 --> 00:16:02,388
[METAL CLANKS]

284
00:16:02,722 --> 00:16:04,155
But I also can't deny

285
00:16:04,188 --> 00:16:06,588
that my time spent with
her has been pleasant.

286
00:16:06,622 --> 00:16:08,488
I quite liked it.

287
00:16:08,522 --> 00:16:09,155
[AL]
But then--

288
00:16:09,188 --> 00:16:10,788
[PRIDE]
As I was saying...

289
00:16:13,455 --> 00:16:16,355
There are a handful of
humans like Wrath's wife...

290
00:16:16,388 --> 00:16:18,355
They're willing to
give up their own lives...

291
00:16:18,388 --> 00:16:21,588
In order to protect the
things they care about.

292
00:16:21,622 --> 00:16:22,788
[METAL CLANKS]

293
00:16:22,822 --> 00:16:25,555
And one step up from them we
have you and your brother...

294
00:16:25,588 --> 00:16:27,455
chosen to be sacrifices

295
00:16:27,488 --> 00:16:30,188
for the infinite strength
of your spirits...

296
00:16:30,222 --> 00:16:33,255
You never would have fled
and abandoned this country...

297
00:16:33,288 --> 00:16:37,288
In fact, you even went so far
as to bring the fight to us.

298
00:16:37,322 --> 00:16:39,522
[METAL CLANKS]

299
00:16:39,555 --> 00:16:44,555
So explain to me again...
How were our plans so sloppy?

300
00:16:44,588 --> 00:16:46,155
[METAL CLANKS]

301
00:16:55,922 --> 00:16:57,388
[HAWKEYE]
Colonel?

302
00:16:59,455 --> 00:17:01,455
We should start
getting ready.

303
00:17:03,322 --> 00:17:04,388
[ROY]
Right.

304
00:17:08,288 --> 00:17:10,322
[HAWKEYE STAMMERS]

305
00:17:11,622 --> 00:17:14,622
Alright then...
Let's move out.

306
00:17:30,503 --> 00:17:31,788
[ZAMPANO]
What happened here?

307
00:17:31,788 --> 00:17:33,555
It's been cleared
to the ground...

308
00:17:33,588 --> 00:17:34,988
the whole area...

309
00:17:35,022 --> 00:17:36,822
And what
caused that?

310
00:17:36,855 --> 00:17:39,055
That's not natural.

311
00:17:39,088 --> 00:17:41,688
[DARIUS]
Hey, is that
Gerso and Zampano?

312
00:17:41,722 --> 00:17:43,688
[ZAMPANO]
What the.... Darius?!

313
00:17:43,722 --> 00:17:44,788
[LOUD THUD]

314
00:17:45,255 --> 00:17:46,255
Let me take a guess...

315
00:17:46,288 --> 00:17:48,788
Kimblee ordered you to
track us down and kill us,

316
00:17:48,822 --> 00:17:49,655
now didn't he?

317
00:17:49,688 --> 00:17:50,222
[DARIUS]
Huh?!

318
00:17:50,255 --> 00:17:51,488
You're joking, right...?

319
00:17:51,522 --> 00:17:54,555
You can't really still think
that we're working for Kimblee?

320
00:17:54,588 --> 00:17:55,688
No way,
of course not...

321
00:17:55,722 --> 00:17:57,988
And as soon as we start
trusting you, you'll kill us.

322
00:17:58,022 --> 00:17:59,655
I would
never do that!

323
00:17:59,688 --> 00:18:00,988
[GERSO]
I'm not fallin' for it...

324
00:18:01,022 --> 00:18:02,922
I bet Heinkel's hiding
around here somewhere,

325
00:18:02,955 --> 00:18:05,022
just waiting for
a chance to ambush us.

326
00:18:05,055 --> 00:18:05,922
[ED]
Dr. Marcoh!

327
00:18:05,955 --> 00:18:06,622
[DARIUS]
You idiot!

328
00:18:06,655 --> 00:18:07,155
[GERSO]
You're the idiot!

329
00:18:07,188 --> 00:18:09,455
[MARCOH]
Oh, Edward!

330
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:12,655
So you're still
working with Scar.

331
00:18:12,688 --> 00:18:14,588
I'm sorry to have to spring
this on you right away,

332
00:18:14,622 --> 00:18:17,655
but we really need to get--

333
00:18:17,688 --> 00:18:19,488
Hey, Piggy,
Gorilla, and Fatty!

334
00:18:19,522 --> 00:18:21,522
Shut up
and stop fighting!

335
00:18:21,555 --> 00:18:23,722
[ALL THREE MEN]
You wanna mess
with us, shorty?!

336
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:27,655
[GERSO]
So you really did quit...?

337
00:18:27,688 --> 00:18:30,522
I guess we all ditched him
around the same time then.

338
00:18:30,555 --> 00:18:31,755
Yeah, sounds
like it...

339
00:18:31,788 --> 00:18:33,688
It was all too
obvious that Kimblee

340
00:18:33,722 --> 00:18:35,922
considered us
to be expendable.

341
00:18:35,955 --> 00:18:37,455
[ALL THREE MEN]
That's the truth.

342
00:18:37,488 --> 00:18:39,522
We may be considered
fugitives now,

343
00:18:39,555 --> 00:18:40,555
but you know what...?

344
00:18:40,588 --> 00:18:42,155
I've got
no complaints.

345
00:18:42,188 --> 00:18:45,488
Same here...
And no matter what...

346
00:18:45,522 --> 00:18:47,722
...I know for
a fact that these guys

347
00:18:47,755 --> 00:18:49,922
would never
abandon us.

348
00:18:54,955 --> 00:18:58,122
[GERSO]
Once the sun comes up...
things are gonna get rough.

349
00:18:58,155 --> 00:18:59,422
I know...

350
00:18:59,455 --> 00:19:03,055
Let's just hope that everyone
makes it through the day alive.

351
00:19:03,088 --> 00:19:04,055
[HEINKEL]
Huh...?

352
00:19:04,088 --> 00:19:06,822
Looks like they've
wrapped up their meeting.

353
00:19:09,022 --> 00:19:11,688
[DARIUS]
Where'd the old
guy head off to?

354
00:19:12,722 --> 00:19:15,055
He's gonna do
some recon in Central.

355
00:19:15,088 --> 00:19:16,455
By himself?

356
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:17,588
Yeah...
He pointed out

357
00:19:17,622 --> 00:19:20,555
that he's the only one who's
kept his identity hidden...

358
00:19:20,588 --> 00:19:23,555
So it'll be easier for him
to infiltrate the city.

359
00:19:24,588 --> 00:19:26,855
[ED]
He also said that he'd
do his best to update us

360
00:19:26,888 --> 00:19:28,955
on Colonel Mustang's actions.

361
00:19:29,755 --> 00:19:31,088
But I'm kind of
getting the feeling that

362
00:19:31,122 --> 00:19:33,188
he's mostly
concerned about Ling.

363
00:19:33,222 --> 00:19:35,455
Sure... That
makes sense.

364
00:19:35,488 --> 00:19:37,055
So you're all finished
discussing things

365
00:19:37,088 --> 00:19:38,755
with Scar
and the others?

366
00:19:38,788 --> 00:19:39,955
That's right.

367
00:19:40,755 --> 00:19:43,122
We've figured
out our strategy.

368
00:19:43,155 --> 00:19:46,422
That so...?
It's almost time, huh?

369
00:19:53,855 --> 00:19:56,655
[GERSO]
Your younger brother's
sure got some serious guts.

370
00:19:56,688 --> 00:19:59,722
[DARIUS]
Trapped in total darkness
with that monster?

371
00:19:59,755 --> 00:20:02,722
I think that I'd lose my
mind if I were in his place.

372
00:20:02,755 --> 00:20:03,788
Yeah.

373
00:20:04,822 --> 00:20:08,788
Al's doing everything
possible to keep us safe...

374
00:20:08,822 --> 00:20:10,822
The rest of it...

375
00:20:10,855 --> 00:20:12,888
Well that's up to us.

376
00:20:30,988 --> 00:20:33,088
[ED THINKING]
<i>The sun has risen...</i>

377
00:20:33,122 --> 00:20:35,588
<i>The Promised Day's begun.</i>

378
00:22:07,122 --> 00:22:09,755
[BROSH'S SISTER]
Brother! Get up, Brother...!

379
00:22:09,788 --> 00:22:11,988
It's time for you
to wake up, Denny!

380
00:22:12,022 --> 00:22:14,022
Pipe down already...

381
00:22:14,055 --> 00:22:15,488
[BROSH]
What time is it?

382
00:22:15,522 --> 00:22:16,855
You have to
get up now...

383
00:22:16,888 --> 00:22:19,022
And hurry up or
you're gonna miss it.

384
00:22:19,055 --> 00:22:21,488
What am I missing...?
Other than sleep?

385
00:22:21,522 --> 00:22:22,888
The solar eclipse!

386
00:22:22,922 --> 00:22:24,788
A solar eclipse?

387
00:22:24,822 --> 00:22:29,122
Oh, man... It's not as
late as you think it is...

388
00:22:29,155 --> 00:22:32,088
I've got plenty of time to
sleep before it starts.

389
00:22:32,122 --> 00:22:35,488
Hey, don't look at the sun...!
You'll blind yourself!

390
00:22:35,522 --> 00:22:37,855
I'm not stupid, Denny.

391
00:22:37,888 --> 00:22:39,588
[BROSH AND HIS SISTER SIGH]

392
00:22:39,622 --> 00:22:41,022
Hey quick,
come check this out!

393
00:22:41,055 --> 00:22:43,055
It looks like there's
a building on fire!

394
00:22:43,088 --> 00:22:44,455
[BROSH GASPS]

395
00:22:48,722 --> 00:22:50,688
[EXPLOSION IN THE DISTANCE]

396
00:22:51,555 --> 00:22:54,422
Do not go outside
the house today, alright?

397
00:22:58,788 --> 00:23:01,088
[EXPLOSION]

398
00:23:01,122 --> 00:23:03,488
[SUBORDINATE 1]
Cedi Squad is currently
engaged in combat

399
00:23:03,522 --> 00:23:05,922
with Mustang's group
in the western sector.

400
00:23:05,955 --> 00:23:07,088
However...

401
00:23:07,122 --> 00:23:09,655
It appears that they've taken
the Fuhrer's wife hostage...

402
00:23:09,688 --> 00:23:11,788
Which has left us
unable to retaliate, sir.

403
00:23:11,822 --> 00:23:13,788
So...?
Go ahead and attack.

404
00:23:13,822 --> 00:23:14,955
Sir?

405
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:20,755
The only one we need
alive is Roy Mustang...

406
00:23:20,788 --> 00:23:23,455
The Fuhrer's wife
is expendable.

407
00:23:23,488 --> 00:23:26,688
Eliminate her along with
Mustang's subordinates.

408
00:23:29,855 --> 00:23:31,688
[GLASS SHATTERS]

409
00:23:32,222 --> 00:23:33,755
[HEAD SOLDIER]
Freeze!

410
00:23:41,988 --> 00:23:43,822
Are you going to shoot?

411
00:23:48,639 --> 00:23:51,072
The only one we need
alive is Mustang...

412
00:23:51,105 --> 00:23:52,772
Kill the rest.

413
00:23:53,605 --> 00:23:54,905
[BRADLEY'S WIFE GASPS]

414
00:23:56,705 --> 00:23:59,372
[GUNSHOT]

415
00:23:59,405 --> 00:24:00,972
[MORE GUNSHOTS]

416
00:24:04,605 --> 00:24:08,439
[NARRATOR]
<i>After living in peace for so</i>
<i>long, the citizens of Amestris</i>

417
00:24:08,472 --> 00:24:12,039
<i>are blind to the impending</i>
<i>peril beneath their feet.</i>

418
00:24:12,072 --> 00:24:16,105
<i>They can't even begin to</i>
imagine their approaching doom.

419
00:24:16,139 --> 00:24:19,439
<i>Next time on Fullmetal</i>
<i>Alchemist: Brotherhood,</i>

420
00:24:19,472 --> 00:24:22,905
<i>Episode Fifty:</i>
<i>Upheaval in Central.</i>

421
00:24:24,139 --> 00:24:26,405
<i>The weak shall lie</i>
<i>down and surrender</i>

422
00:24:26,439 --> 00:24:29,005
<i>while the strong trample</i>
<i>over their bodies...</i>

423
00:24:29,039 --> 00:24:32,372
This is the simple fact of war.

